# NASA Space Mission Classification — Project Summary

This project focuses on building a machine learning model to classify NASA space missions based on mission data. The goal was to understand how supervised learning can be applied to real-world scientific datasets and to practice the full ML workflow from preprocessing to evaluation.

## Objective
To classify NASA missions into categories using structured mission data and machine learning techniques.

## What I Did
- Cleaned and preprocessed the dataset (handling missing values, encoding categories, scaling features).
- Performed exploratory data analysis to understand mission patterns.
- Engineered features to improve model performance.
- Trained multiple classification models and compared their accuracy.
- Evaluated results using metrics such as accuracy, confusion matrix, and classification report.

## Key Learnings
- How to build an end-to-end ML pipeline.
- How preprocessing affects model performance.
- How to compare models and choose the best one.
- How ML can support scientific research and mission planning.

## Outcome
A working classification model capable of predicting mission categories with strong accuracy, demonstrating practical machine learning skills and real-world data handling.
